  "original_title": "\u0bb5\u0bc6\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1 \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0ba3\u0baf \u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf \u0bb5\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b85\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Central Bank of Sri Lanka announces foreign currency reserves",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Central Bank of Sri Lanka has issued a notification regarding the holding of foreign currencies.",
        "The maximum amount of foreign currency a person can hold in Sri Lanka has been reduced from US $ 15,000 to US $ 10,000.",
        "Meanwhile, the Central Bank of Sri Lanka has stated that it has the right to take action against holders of excess foreign currency.",
        "It is pertinent to note that on the 16th of this month, a gazette notification was issued regarding the reduction of the amount of foreign currency held by a person in or residing in Sri Lanka from US $ 15,000 to US $ 10,000 or equivalent in other foreign currencies."
      ],
      "title_ents": [
